	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A lot of my NES programs detect Nesticle (using the PPUSTATUS bug) and throw up a dialog box warning the player of possible incompatibility (press start to continue anyway). Is there a way for a program to <em>detect</em> a poorly designed clone and throw up a dialog box, or is there a way for a board to detect a poorly designed clone and make it visible to the program?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
